    "what_description": "Trichosalpinx triangulipetala is a species of epiphytic orchid in the family Orchidaceae, native to Central America. It has a terete, glabrous, and cylindrical pseudobulb, 2.5-4.5 cm long and 0.6-1.2 cm in diameter, with 2-3 fleshy, triangular, and petiolate leaves at the apex. The inflorescence is a raceme, 1.5-2.5 cm long, with 2-4 flowers. The flowers are greenish-yellow, 0.5-0.7 cm in diameter, with a yellow labellum and a white, fleshy, and spurred column. The plant flowers in the summer months.",
